<p>More than one in four people on the planet have some degree of nonalcoholic steatohepatitis, NASH, or its precursor, known as nonalcoholic fatty liver disease, or NAFLD. NAFLD is highly correlated with both obesity and hyperlipidemia (excessive cholesterol), yet it often flies under the radar, especially in its early stages.</p>
